Mvita MP Abdulswamad Nassir on Sunday pledged to supply the Shimo la Tewa Women Prison with a six-month ration of milk and diapers forwomen  inmates jailed with their children. The facility, has 250 women, lacks basic supply of milk and diapers and the women are forced to share their meal swith their children. Nassir was speaking during an Easter luncheon organized by Virtual Volunteers Foundation. “We are going to arrange for a date, within a week or two, we will get donors and at least have the milk and diapers supplied to these children,” he said.